Description: Lip and wall sherd of East Greek pottery bowl-shaped cup; interior: dark brown glaze with added red stripe; exterior: top of rim glazed; lip zone reserved with glazed area below; inscription cut on exterior, in reserved zone.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 323)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 670, no. 284)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.370)
